  "featureInfoProductsTitle": "Products Management",
  "featureInfoProductsDesc": "Manage your entire product catalog from here. You can add new products, edit existing ones, set pricing, manage variants and barcodes, and organize products by categories. Products can be searched by name, SKU, or barcode.",
  "featureInfoProductsAddTitle": "Adding a New Product",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep1Title": "Tap the Add Product button",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button (+ icon) at the bottom of the screen to open the product form.",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep2Title": "Fill in Basic Info",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep2Desc": "Enter the product name (required), optional Arabic name, description, select a category, choose the unit type, enter SKU, and scan or type the barcode. Set minimum/maximum order quantities if needed.",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep3Title": "Set Pricing",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep3Desc": "Go to the Pricing tab. Enter the sell price (required) and cost price. Set the tax rate percentage. The margin and profit are calculated automatically. You can also set offer prices with start/end dates.",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep4Title": "Add Media",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep4Desc": "Go to the Media tab to add a product image URL. A live preview will show the image.",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep5Title": "Save the Product",
  "featureInfoProductsAddStep5Desc": "Tap 'Create Product' at the bottom. After saving, you can manage variants, modifiers, barcodes, and suppliers from the additional tabs.",
  "featureInfoProductsEditTitle": "Editing a Product",
  "featureInfoProductsEditStep1Title": "Find the product",
  "featureInfoProductsEditStep1Desc": "Use the search bar to search by name, SKU, or barcode. You can also filter by category using the sidebar (desktop) or category chips (mobile).",
  "featureInfoProductsEditStep2Title": "Open the edit form",
  "featureInfoProductsEditStep2Desc": "Click the 'Edit' action on the product row, or tap the product on mobile. This opens the product form with all existing data pre-filled.",
  "featureInfoProductsEditStep3Title": "Update and save",
  "featureInfoProductsEditStep3Desc": "Make your changes across any tab (Basic Info, Pricing, Variants, Modifiers, Barcodes, Suppliers, Media) and tap 'Update Product'.",
  "featureInfoProductsDeleteTitle": "Deleting a Product",
  "featureInfoProductsDeleteStep1Title": "Select products to delete",
  "featureInfoProductsDeleteStep1Desc": "Use the 'Delete' action on an individual product row, or select multiple products using checkboxes and use the 'Delete' bulk action.",
  "featureInfoProductsDeleteStep2Title": "Confirm deletion",
  "featureInfoProductsDeleteStep2Desc": "A confirmation dialog will appear. Products are soft-deleted and can potentially be recovered. Confirm to proceed.",
  "featureInfoProductsTip1": "Use the grid/list toggle (desktop) to switch between table and card views.",
  "featureInfoProductsTip2": "You can duplicate products using the 'Duplicate' row action to quickly create similar items.",
  "featureInfoProductsTip3": "Bulk actions (activate, deactivate, delete) are available when you select multiple products.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesTitle": "Categories Management",
  "featureInfoCategoriesDesc": "Organize your products with a hierarchical category tree. Categories support parent-child relationships, allowing you to create a structured product taxonomy. Each category can have a name in both English and Arabic.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddTitle": "Creating a Category",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep1Title": "Tap the New Category button",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to open the category creation dialog.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep2Title": "Fill in category details",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep2Desc": "Enter the category name (required), Arabic name, description, and Arabic description. Choose a parent category if you want to create a sub-category.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep3Title": "Set display order",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep3Desc": "Set the sort order number to control the display order among sibling categories. Toggle active status on or off.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep4Title": "Save the category",
  "featureInfoCategoriesAddStep4Desc": "Tap 'Save' to create the category. It will appear in the tree under its parent.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesEditTitle": "Editing a Category",
  "featureInfoCategoriesEditStep1Title": "Click Edit on the category",
  "featureInfoCategoriesEditStep1Desc": "Find the category in the tree view and click the 'Edit' action. The dialog opens pre-filled with current data.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesEditStep2Title": "Update and save",
  "featureInfoCategoriesEditStep2Desc": "Change the name, parent, sort order, or active status and tap 'Save'. You can move categories to different parents.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesDeleteTitle": "Deleting a Category",
  "featureInfoCategoriesDeleteStep1Title": "Click Delete on the category",
  "featureInfoCategoriesDeleteStep1Desc": "Find the category in the tree and click 'Delete'. A warning will appear if the category has subcategories.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesDeleteStep2Title": "Confirm deletion",
  "featureInfoCategoriesDeleteStep2Desc": "Review the warning about subcategories and confirm. Subcategories may be reassigned or deleted depending on your configuration.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesTip1": "Use 'Expand All' and 'Collapse All' buttons in the AppBar to quickly navigate the category tree.",
  "featureInfoCategoriesTip2": "You can add child categories directly from any tree node using the 'Add Child' action.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersTitle": "Suppliers Management",
  "featureInfoSuppliersDesc": "Manage your supplier directory with full contact details, banking information, and business settings. Track purchase orders, goods receipts, returns, and outstanding balances for each supplier.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddTitle": "Adding a New Supplier",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep1Title": "Tap the New Supplier button",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to open the supplier form dialog.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep2Title": "Enter basic information",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep2Desc": "Fill in the supplier name (required), contact person, and category.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep3Title": "Add contact and banking details",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep3Desc": "Enter phone, email, website, address, and banking information (bank name, account, IBAN). Add the tax number, payment terms, credit limit, and any notes.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep4Title": "Save the supplier",
  "featureInfoSuppliersAddStep4Desc": "Tap 'Save' to add the supplier to your directory.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersEditTitle": "Editing a Supplier",
  "featureInfoSuppliersEditStep1Title": "Click Edit on the supplier row",
  "featureInfoSuppliersEditStep1Desc": "Find the supplier in the table and click 'Edit'. The dialog opens pre-filled.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersEditStep2Title": "Update and save",
  "featureInfoSuppliersEditStep2Desc": "Modify any field and tap 'Save' to update the supplier.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersDeleteTitle": "Deleting a Supplier",
  "featureInfoSuppliersDeleteStep1Title": "Click Delete on the supplier row",
  "featureInfoSuppliersDeleteStep1Desc": "Find the supplier in the table and click the 'Delete' action.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersDeleteStep2Title": "Confirm deletion",
  "featureInfoSuppliersDeleteStep2Desc": "Confirm the deletion in the dialog. Note: this may affect linked products and purchase orders.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersTip1": "Tap a supplier row to see detailed statistics including purchase orders, goods receipts, returns, and outstanding balance.",
  "featureInfoSuppliersTip2": "Use the search bar to quickly find suppliers by name.",
  "featureInfoCustomersTitle": "Customer Directory",
  "featureInfoCustomersDesc": "View your customer list showing customer names, contact information, and loyalty points. Customers are added automatically when they make purchases or can be added from the POS terminal during checkout.",
  "featureInfoCustomersViewTitle": "Viewing Customers",
  "featureInfoCustomersViewStep1Title": "Browse the customer list",
  "featureInfoCustomersViewStep1Desc": "Scroll through the customer list to see names, email or phone numbers, and loyalty points for each customer.",
  "featureInfoCustomersViewStep2Title": "Check customer details",
  "featureInfoCustomersViewStep2Desc": "Each customer card shows their name, contact info, and accumulated loyalty points.",
  "featureInfoCustomersTip1": "Customers can be attached to orders from the POS cashier screen during checkout using the customer search button.",
  "featureInfoOrdersTitle": "Orders Management",
  "featureInfoOrdersDesc": "View and manage all orders across your store. Filter orders by status, search by order number, and void orders when needed. Orders are created from the POS terminal and appear here with their full details.",
  "featureInfoOrdersViewTitle": "Viewing Orders",
  "featureInfoOrdersViewStep1Title": "Browse the order list",
  "featureInfoOrdersViewStep1Desc": "View all orders in a table (desktop) or card list (mobile) with order number, source, status, subtotal, tax, total, and date.",
  "featureInfoOrdersViewStep2Title": "Search by order number",
  "featureInfoOrdersViewStep2Desc": "Use the search bar to find a specific order by its order number.",
  "featureInfoOrdersViewStep3Title": "Filter by status",
  "featureInfoOrdersViewStep3Desc": "Use the filter icon in the AppBar to filter orders by status: All, New, Confirmed, Preparing, Ready, Completed, Cancelled, or Voided.",
  "featureInfoOrdersVoidTitle": "Voiding an Order",
  "featureInfoOrdersVoidStep1Title": "Find the order to void",
  "featureInfoOrdersVoidStep1Desc": "Locate the order in the list. The void action is only available for orders that are not already voided or cancelled.",
  "featureInfoOrdersVoidStep2Title": "Confirm the void",
  "featureInfoOrdersVoidStep2Desc": "Click the 'Void' action on the order row and confirm in the dialog. This is irreversible.",
  "featureInfoOrdersTip1": "Use pagination controls at the bottom to navigate between pages.",
  "featureInfoOrdersTip2": "Pull down to refresh the order list on mobile.",
  "featureInfoStaffTitle": "Staff Management",
  "featureInfoStaffDesc": "Manage your team members with full profiles, employment details, PIN security, and user accounts. Staff can be filtered by store, status, and employment type. Each staff member can have a POS PIN for secure access.",
  "featureInfoStaffAddTitle": "Adding a Staff Member",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep1Title": "Tap the Add button",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to navigate to the staff creation form.",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep2Title": "Select store and fill personal info",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep2Desc": "Choose the store assignment from the dropdown. Enter the first name (required) and last name (required).",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep3Title": "Set contact and employment details",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep3Desc": "Enter email (required if creating a user account), phone, and national ID. Select the employment type (full-time, part-time, etc.), salary type, hourly rate (if applicable), status, and hire date.",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep4Title": "Configure Security PIN",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep4Desc": "Set a 4-6 digit PIN that the staff member will use to log in to the POS terminal.",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep5Title": "Create optional user account",
  "featureInfoStaffAddStep5Desc": "Toggle 'Create User Account' to enable system login. Select a role (e.g. cashier) and set a password (minimum 8 characters). Tap 'Create Member' to save.",
  "featureInfoStaffEditTitle": "Editing a Staff Member",
  "featureInfoStaffEditStep1Title": "Find and open the staff profile",
  "featureInfoStaffEditStep1Desc": "Use the store selector, search bar, or filter chips (status/employment type) to find the staff member. Tap the card or select 'Edit' from the popup menu.",
  "featureInfoStaffEditStep2Title": "Update and save",
  "featureInfoStaffEditStep2Desc": "Modify any field and tap 'Save Changes'. You can also change the PIN using the 'Change PIN' button.",
  "featureInfoStaffDeleteTitle": "Deleting a Staff Member",
  "featureInfoStaffDeleteStep1Title": "Open the staff popup menu",
  "featureInfoStaffDeleteStep1Desc": "Find the staff member card and tap the three-dot menu icon.",
  "featureInfoStaffDeleteStep2Title": "Select Delete and confirm",
  "featureInfoStaffDeleteStep2Desc": "Choose 'Delete' from the menu and confirm in the dialog.",
  "featureInfoStaffTip1": "Use the store selector at the top to view staff for a specific branch.",
  "featureInfoStaffTip2": "Filter chips let you quickly filter by status (Active, Inactive, On Leave) or employment type.",
  "featureInfoStaffTip3": "The PIN is essential for POS terminal access — make sure each staff member has a unique PIN.",
  "featureInfoRolesTitle": "Roles & Permissions",
  "featureInfoRolesDesc": "Define roles with granular permissions to control what each staff member can access. System-predefined roles cannot be deleted. Create custom roles with specific permission sets for your team.",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateTitle": "Creating a New Role",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New Role button",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to navigate to the role creation form.",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep2Title": "Enter role name and description",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep2Desc": "Type a display name for the role (e.g. 'Shift Manager'). The system name is auto-generated. Optionally add a description.",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep3Title": "Select permissions",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep3Desc": "Expand each permission module (POS, Orders, Inventory, Catalog, Customers, Reports, Staff, Settings, Accounting, Kitchen, Promotions) and check individual permissions. Use the select-all checkbox per module for quick selection.",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep4Title": "Save the role",
  "featureInfoRolesCreateStep4Desc": "Tap 'Create' in the AppBar. The role is now available for assignment to staff members.",
  "featureInfoRolesDeleteTitle": "Deleting a Custom Role",
  "featureInfoRolesDeleteStep1Title": "Find the custom role",
  "featureInfoRolesDeleteStep1Desc": "Custom roles show a delete icon on their card. System-predefined roles (marked with 'System' badge) cannot be deleted.",
  "featureInfoRolesDeleteStep2Title": "Confirm deletion",
  "featureInfoRolesDeleteStep2Desc": "Tap the delete icon and confirm. Make sure no staff members are currently assigned this role before deleting.",
  "featureInfoRolesTip1": "Some permissions are marked as 'Requires PIN override' — these need extra verification at the POS.",
  "featureInfoRolesTip2": "System roles (Owner, Manager, Cashier, etc.) are pre-configured and cannot be deleted, but you can view their permissions.",
  "featureInfoInventoryTitle": "Inventory Management",
  "featureInfoInventoryDesc": "Your central hub for all inventory operations. Access Stock Levels, Stock Movements, Goods Receipts, Stock Adjustments, Stock Transfers, Purchase Orders, Recipes, and Supplier Returns from the tiles below.",
  "featureInfoInventoryNavigateTitle": "Using the Inventory Hub",
  "featureInfoInventoryNavigateStep1Title": "Choose an inventory module",
  "featureInfoInventoryNavigateStep1Desc": "Tap any of the 8 tiles to navigate to that module: Stock Levels, Stock Movements, Goods Receipts, Stock Adjustments, Stock Transfers, Purchase Orders, Recipes, or Supplier Returns.",
  "featureInfoInventoryNavigateStep2Title": "Use each module",
  "featureInfoInventoryNavigateStep2Desc": "Each module has its own info button (ℹ) with detailed instructions for that specific feature.",
  "featureInfoInventoryTip1": "Stock Levels shows current quantities and reorder status at a glance.",
  "featureInfoInventoryTip2": "Stock Movements is read-only — it automatically logs all inventory changes across the system.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjTitle": "Stock Adjustments",
  "featureInfoStockAdjDesc": "Record manual changes to inventory quantities. Use adjustments for stock count corrections, damaged goods, expired items, theft, or any other reason that changes your actual stock without a purchase or sale.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateTitle": "Creating a Stock Adjustment",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New Adjustment button",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to open the adjustment dialog.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep2Title": "Select the adjustment type",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep2Desc": "Choose 'Increase' to add stock, 'Decrease' to reduce stock, or 'Damage' to record damaged goods.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep3Title": "Select the product",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep3Desc": "Use the searchable product dropdown to find and select the product you want to adjust.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep4Title": "Enter quantity and reason",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep4Desc": "Enter the quantity to adjust. Select a reason: Damaged, Expired, Lost, Correction, Returned, Miscounted, Theft, or Other. Optionally add notes.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep5Title": "Submit the adjustment",
  "featureInfoStockAdjCreateStep5Desc": "Tap 'Create' to record the adjustment. The stock level will be updated immediately.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjTip1": "Always select the correct reason — it helps in reporting and audit trails.",
  "featureInfoStockAdjTip2": "Use 'Correction' when fixing count discrepancies found during physical inventory counts.",
  "featureInfoPOTitle": "Purchase Orders",
  "featureInfoPODesc": "Create and manage purchase orders for your suppliers. Track orders through their lifecycle: Draft → Sent → Partially Received → Fully Received. Filter by status and manage the full procurement workflow.",
  "featureInfoPOCreateTitle": "Creating a Purchase Order",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New PO button",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to open the purchase order creation dialog.",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep2Title": "Select a supplier",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep2Desc": "Use the searchable dropdown to find and select the supplier for this order.",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep3Title": "Add product and quantities",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep3Desc": "Optionally enter a reference number. Select the product, enter the quantity and unit cost.",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep4Title": "Create the order",
  "featureInfoPOCreateStep4Desc": "Tap 'Create' to save the purchase order as a Draft.",
  "featureInfoPOManageTitle": "Managing Purchase Orders",
  "featureInfoPOManageStep1Title": "Send the order",
  "featureInfoPOManageStep1Desc": "When ready, use the 'Send' action on a Draft order to mark it as Sent to the supplier.",
  "featureInfoPOManageStep2Title": "Receive the order",
  "featureInfoPOManageStep2Desc": "When goods arrive, use the 'Receive' action on a Sent order to mark it as Received. Stock levels update automatically.",
  "featureInfoPOManageStep3Title": "Cancel if needed",
  "featureInfoPOManageStep3Desc": "Draft or Sent orders can be cancelled using the 'Cancel' action with a confirmation dialog.",
  "featureInfoPOTip1": "Use the filter button to view orders by status (Draft, Sent, Partially Received, Fully Received, Cancelled).",
  "featureInfoPOTip2": "The table shows reference number, supplier, status, total cost, and expected delivery date.",
  "featureInfoTransfersTitle": "Stock Transfers",
  "featureInfoTransfersDesc": "Transfer stock between your store branches. Track transfers through the approval workflow: Pending → Approved → In Transit → Received. Each transfer requires source and destination stores.",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateTitle": "Creating a Stock Transfer",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New Transfer button",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to open the transfer creation dialog.",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep2Title": "Select source and destination",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep2Desc": "Choose the 'From Store' (source branch) and 'To Store' (destination branch) from the searchable dropdowns.",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep3Title": "Add product details",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep3Desc": "Select the product to transfer, enter the quantity, and optionally add notes.",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep4Title": "Create the transfer",
  "featureInfoTransfersCreateStep4Desc": "Tap 'Create' to submit the transfer request as Pending.",
  "featureInfoTransfersManageTitle": "Managing Stock Transfers",
  "featureInfoTransfersManageStep1Title": "Approve the transfer",
  "featureInfoTransfersManageStep1Desc": "Use the 'Approve' action on Pending transfers. This changes the status to In Transit.",
  "featureInfoTransfersManageStep2Title": "Receive the transfer",
  "featureInfoTransfersManageStep2Desc": "When the goods arrive at the destination, use the 'Receive' action. Stock levels are updated at both stores.",
  "featureInfoTransfersManageStep3Title": "Cancel if needed",
  "featureInfoTransfersManageStep3Desc": "Pending transfers can be cancelled using the 'Cancel' action. Transfers that are already in transit cannot be cancelled.",
  "featureInfoTransfersTip1": "The table shows reference number, source store, destination store, status, and creation date.",
  "featureInfoGRTitle": "Goods Receipts",
  "featureInfoGRDesc": "Record incoming goods from suppliers. Goods receipts update your inventory stock levels when confirmed. Receipts start as Draft and can be confirmed when verified.",
  "featureInfoGRCreateTitle": "Creating a Goods Receipt",
  "featureInfoGRCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New Receipt button",
  "featureInfoGRCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to navigate to the goods receipt form page.",
  "featureInfoGRCreateStep2Title": "Fill in receipt details",
  "featureInfoGRCreateStep2Desc": "Select the supplier, enter reference number, add the received products with quantities and costs.",
  "featureInfoGRCreateStep3Title": "Save as Draft",
  "featureInfoGRCreateStep3Desc": "Save the receipt. It will be created as a Draft that can be reviewed before confirmation.",
  "featureInfoGRConfirmTitle": "Confirming a Goods Receipt",
  "featureInfoGRConfirmStep1Title": "Find the draft receipt",
  "featureInfoGRConfirmStep1Desc": "Locate the Draft receipt in the table. Only Draft receipts can be confirmed.",
  "featureInfoGRConfirmStep2Title": "Confirm the receipt",
  "featureInfoGRConfirmStep2Desc": "Click the 'Confirm' action and verify in the dialog. Stock levels will be updated with the received quantities.",
  "featureInfoGRTip1": "The table shows reference number, supplier, status, total cost, and received date with pagination.",
  "featureInfoSRTitle": "Supplier Returns",
  "featureInfoSRDesc": "Process returns of goods back to suppliers. Returns follow a workflow: Draft → Submitted → Approved → Completed. Search and filter returns by status to track the return process.",
  "featureInfoSRCreateTitle": "Creating a Supplier Return",
  "featureInfoSRCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New Return button",
  "featureInfoSRCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to navigate to the supplier return form page.",
  "featureInfoSRCreateStep2Title": "Fill in return details",
  "featureInfoSRCreateStep2Desc": "Select the supplier, enter a reason for the return, and add the products being returned with quantities and costs.",
  "featureInfoSRCreateStep3Title": "Save as Draft",
  "featureInfoSRCreateStep3Desc": "Save the return. It starts as a Draft that you can review and edit before submitting.",
  "featureInfoSRManageTitle": "Managing Supplier Returns",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep1Title": "Submit the return",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep1Desc": "Use the 'Submit' action on a Draft return to send it for approval.",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep2Title": "Approve the return",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep2Desc": "Use the 'Approve' action on a Submitted return to authorize the return.",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep3Title": "Complete the return",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep3Desc": "Use the 'Complete' action on an Approved return to finalize it. Stock levels are adjusted accordingly.",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep4Title": "Cancel or delete if needed",
  "featureInfoSRManageStep4Desc": "Draft and Submitted returns can be cancelled. Draft returns can also be permanently deleted.",
  "featureInfoSRTip1": "Use the search bar and status filter dropdown to quickly find specific returns.",
  "featureInfoRecipesTitle": "Recipes",
  "featureInfoRecipesDesc": "Define recipes that tie a finished product to its raw material ingredients. This helps track ingredient consumption and manage composite product costs. Each recipe specifies the output product, yield quantity, ingredients, and waste percentage.",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateTitle": "Creating a Recipe",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New Recipe button",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to open the recipe creation dialog.",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep2Title": "Select the output product",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep2Desc": "Use the searchable dropdown to select the finished product that this recipe produces.",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep3Title": "Set the yield quantity",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep3Desc": "Enter how many units of the output product this recipe produces (default is 1).",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep4Title": "Add ingredients",
  "featureInfoRecipesCreateStep4Desc": "Select the ingredient product, enter the ingredient quantity, and set the waste percentage (how much material is typically wasted). Tap 'Create' to save.",
  "featureInfoRecipesDeleteTitle": "Deleting a Recipe",
  "featureInfoRecipesDeleteStep1Title": "Find the recipe in the table",
  "featureInfoRecipesDeleteStep1Desc": "Locate the recipe you want to delete in the list showing product name, yield, and status.",
  "featureInfoRecipesDeleteStep2Title": "Delete and confirm",
  "featureInfoRecipesDeleteStep2Desc": "Click the 'Delete' action and confirm in the dialog. This removes the recipe definition.",
  "featureInfoRecipesTip1": "Set the waste percentage to account for material lost during production (e.g. trimming, evaporation).",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsTitle": "Stock Levels",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsDesc": "Monitor current stock quantities for all products. View available and reserved stock, average cost, and reorder status. Set reorder points and maximum stock levels to get alerts when stock is low.",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsViewTitle": "Viewing Stock Levels",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsViewStep1Title": "Browse the stock table",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsViewStep1Desc": "View product name, quantity, reserved stock, average cost, reorder point, and status (Low Stock or OK) in the table.",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsViewStep2Title": "Filter low stock items",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsViewStep2Desc": "Toggle the 'Low Stock' filter chip to show only products that are below their reorder point.",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsReorderTitle": "Setting Reorder Points",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsReorderStep1Title": "Click 'Set Reorder Point'",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsReorderStep1Desc": "Use the row action 'Set Reorder Point' on any product to open the dialog.",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsReorderStep2Title": "Enter reorder thresholds",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsReorderStep2Desc": "Set the reorder point (minimum stock level before alert) and optionally set the maximum stock level.",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsReorderStep3Title": "Save the thresholds",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsReorderStep3Desc": "Tap 'Save'. Products below the reorder point will show a 'Low Stock' badge.",
  "featureInfoStockLevelsTip1": "Use the search bar to find specific products and the pagination controls to navigate large inventories.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsTitle": "Promotions & Coupons",
  "featureInfoPromotionsDesc": "Create and manage promotions to boost sales. Supports percentage discounts, fixed amount discounts, buy-one-get-one (BOGO), bundle deals, and happy hour pricing. Generate coupon codes and track performance analytics.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateTitle": "Creating a Promotion",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep1Title": "Tap the Add button",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to open the promotion creation form.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep2Title": "Enter promotion details",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep2Desc": "Enter the promotion name (required) and description. Select the type: Percentage, Fixed Amount, BOGO, Bundle, or Happy Hour.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep3Title": "Configure discount values",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep3Desc": "Based on the type selected: enter discount % or amount for percentage/fixed; set buy quantity, get quantity, and get discount % for BOGO; enter bundle price for bundles.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep4Title": "Set rules and limits",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep4Desc": "Configure minimum order total, maximum total uses, and maximum uses per customer. Toggle 'Requires Coupon Code' if this is a coupon-based promotion. Toggle 'Stackable' to allow combining with other promotions.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep5Title": "Save the promotion",
  "featureInfoPromotionsCreateStep5Desc": "Tap 'Save' to create the promotion. It can be activated or deactivated at any time.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsManageTitle": "Managing Promotions",
  "featureInfoPromotionsManageStep1Title": "Toggle active/inactive",
  "featureInfoPromotionsManageStep1Desc": "Use the switch on each promotion card to instantly activate or deactivate it.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsManageStep2Title": "Generate coupons",
  "featureInfoPromotionsManageStep2Desc": "For coupon-based promotions, use 'Generate Coupons' from the popup menu. Set the count, prefix, and max uses per coupon.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsManageStep3Title": "View analytics",
  "featureInfoPromotionsManageStep3Desc": "Select 'Analytics' from the popup menu to see performance data for the promotion.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsTip1": "Use the search bar and filter button to find promotions by name, type, or status.",
  "featureInfoPromotionsTip2": "Happy hour promotions automatically apply during configured time windows.",
  "featureInfoBranchesTitle": "Branches Management",
  "featureInfoBranchesDesc": "Manage all your store branches and warehouses. Configure branch details including location, contact info, operational settings, legal documents, and social media profiles. View statistics for active and inactive branches.",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateTitle": "Creating a Branch",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep1Title": "Tap the Create Branch button",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to navigate to the branch creation form.",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep2Title": "Fill in Basic Info",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep2Desc": "Enter branch name (required), Arabic name, branch code, description, business type, timezone, currency, and locale. Set flags like Is Main Branch, Is Warehouse, Accepts Online Orders, etc.",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep3Title": "Set Location details",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep3Desc": "Enter the address, city, region, postal code, country, Google Maps URL, and coordinates (latitude/longitude).",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep4Title": "Add Contact information",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep4Desc": "Enter phone, secondary phone, email, and contact person for the branch.",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep5Title": "Configure Operational settings",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep5Desc": "Set opening/closing dates, max registers, max staff, floor area, seating capacity, and upload logo/cover images.",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep6Title": "Add Legal and Social info",
  "featureInfoBranchesCreateStep6Desc": "Enter CR number, VAT number, municipal license, license expiry. Add social media profiles (Instagram, Twitter, Facebook, etc.). Tap 'Save' to create.",
  "featureInfoBranchesEditTitle": "Editing a Branch",
  "featureInfoBranchesEditStep1Title": "Find and tap the branch",
  "featureInfoBranchesEditStep1Desc": "Use the search bar or status filter to find the branch. Tap the branch card to open its detail page.",
  "featureInfoBranchesEditStep2Title": "Edit and save",
  "featureInfoBranchesEditStep2Desc": "Modify any fields across all 6 tabs and tap 'Save' to update.",
  "featureInfoBranchesTip1": "The stats row at the top shows total branches, active count, inactive count, and warehouse count.",
  "featureInfoBranchesTip2": "Use the status filter (All/Active/Inactive) to quickly narrow down the branch list.",
  "featureInfoDebitsTitle": "Debits Management",
  "featureInfoDebitsDesc": "Track customer credits, supplier returns, inventory adjustments, and manual credits. Debits represent money owed that can be allocated to orders. View summary KPIs for total, pending, allocated, and unallocated amounts.",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateTitle": "Creating a Debit",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep1Title": "Tap the Add button",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep1Desc": "Press the floating action button to navigate to the debit creation form.",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep2Title": "Select customer and type",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep2Desc": "Choose the customer from the searchable dropdown. Select the debit type: Customer Credit, Supplier Return, Inventory Adjustment, or Manual Credit.",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep3Title": "Enter amount and details",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep3Desc": "Select the source (POS Terminal, Invoice, Return, Manual, Inventory System). Enter the amount, reference number, and descriptions in both English and Arabic.",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep4Title": "Save the debit",
  "featureInfoDebitsCreateStep4Desc": "Tap 'Save' to create the debit with Pending status.",
  "featureInfoDebitsAllocateTitle": "Allocating a Debit to an Order",
  "featureInfoDebitsAllocateStep1Title": "Find the pending debit",
  "featureInfoDebitsAllocateStep1Desc": "Use the status and type filters in the AppBar to find debits that can be allocated.",
  "featureInfoDebitsAllocateStep2Title": "Click the Allocate action",
  "featureInfoDebitsAllocateStep2Desc": "On a pending or partially allocated debit, click the 'Allocate' row action to open the allocation dialog.",
  "featureInfoDebitsAllocateStep3Title": "Select order and amount",
  "featureInfoDebitsAllocateStep3Desc": "Choose the order to allocate to, enter the amount (up to remaining balance), add optional notes, and confirm.",
  "featureInfoDebitsReverseTitle": "Reversing a Debit",
  "featureInfoDebitsReverseStep1Title": "Click the Reverse action",
  "featureInfoDebitsReverseStep1Desc": "On an eligible debit, click the 'Reverse' action to open the reversal dialog.",
  "featureInfoDebitsReverseStep2Title": "Enter reason and confirm",
  "featureInfoDebitsReverseStep2Desc": "Type the reversal reason and confirm. Reversed debits cannot be allocated.",
  "featureInfoDebitsTip1": "The summary cards at the top show Total Debits, Pending Amount, Allocated, and Unallocated totals.",
  "featureInfoDebitsTip2": "Use the search bar to find debits by reference number.",
  "featureInfoExpensesTitle": "Expenses Tracking",
  "featureInfoExpensesDesc": "Record and track your store's daily expenses. Expenses are grouped by date with daily totals. Categories include Supplies, Food, Transport, Maintenance, Utility, and Other.",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateTitle": "Recording an Expense",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep1Title": "Tap the New Expense button",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep1Desc": "Click the 'New Expense' button in the AppBar to open the expense dialog.",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep2Title": "Enter the amount",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep2Desc": "Type the expense amount in the numeric field.",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep3Title": "Select a category",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep3Desc": "Choose from: Supplies, Food, Transport, Maintenance, Utility, or Other.",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep4Title": "Add description and save",
  "featureInfoExpensesCreateStep4Desc": "Optionally add a description explaining the expense. Tap 'Create' to record it.",
  "featureInfoExpensesTip1": "Expenses are grouped by date. Each date group shows the total expenses for that day.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtTitle": "Cash Management",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtDesc": "Manage cash sessions for your POS terminal. Open a session at the start of a shift, record cash-in and cash-out events during the day, count denominations, and close the session at the end of the shift.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtOpenTitle": "Opening a Cash Session",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtOpenStep1Title": "Tap 'Open Session'",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtOpenStep1Desc": "If no active session exists, tap the 'Open Session' button to start.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtOpenStep2Title": "Enter opening float",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtOpenStep2Desc": "Enter the amount of cash in the drawer at the start of the session (opening float) and confirm.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCashInOutTitle": "Recording Cash In/Out",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCashInOutStep1Title": "Tap Cash In or Cash Out",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCashInOutStep1Desc": "With an active session, use the 'Cash In' or 'Cash Out' buttons on the session card.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCashInOutStep2Title": "Enter details",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCashInOutStep2Desc": "Enter the amount, select a reason (for Cash In: tips, change replenish, other; for Cash Out: petty cash, supplier payment, bank deposit, other), and optionally add notes.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCashInOutStep3Title": "Submit the transaction",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCashInOutStep3Desc": "Confirm the cash event. The expected cash balance updates in real-time.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCloseTitle": "Closing a Cash Session",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCloseStep1Title": "Count your cash",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCloseStep1Desc": "Use the denomination counter to count all cash in the drawer by entering quantities for each note and coin denomination.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCloseStep2Title": "Tap 'Close Session'",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCloseStep2Desc": "Review the counted total and expected cash amount. Optionally add closing notes.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCloseStep3Title": "Confirm the closure",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtCloseStep3Desc": "Confirm to close the session. Any variance between counted and expected cash is recorded.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtTip1": "The denomination counter helps you accurately count physical cash before closing the session.",
  "featureInfoCashMgmtTip2": "Session history at the bottom shows previous sessions with opening float, timing, and variance.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsTitle": "Gift Cards",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsDesc": "Issue, check, and redeem gift cards for your store. Gift cards have a unique code, balance, optional recipient name, and expiry date. Three tabs let you manage the full gift card lifecycle.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsIssueTitle": "Issuing a Gift Card",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsIssueStep1Title": "Select an amount",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsIssueStep1Desc": "On the 'Issue' tab, choose a quick preset amount (50, 100, 200, 500) or enter a custom amount.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsIssueStep2Title": "Add recipient (optional)",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsIssueStep2Desc": "Enter the recipient's name if you want to personalize the gift card.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsIssueStep3Title": "Issue the card",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsIssueStep3Desc": "Tap 'Issue Gift Card'. A result card appears showing the generated code, initial amount, balance, and status.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsCheckTitle": "Checking Balance",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsCheckStep1Title": "Enter the gift card code",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsCheckStep1Desc": "On the 'Check Balance' tab, enter the gift card code.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsCheckStep2Title": "View balance details",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsCheckStep2Desc": "Tap 'Check'. The remaining balance, status, and expiry date are displayed.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsRedeemTitle": "Redeeming a Gift Card",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsRedeemStep1Title": "Enter the gift card code",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsRedeemStep1Desc": "On the 'Redeem' tab, enter the gift card code.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsRedeemStep2Title": "Enter redemption amount",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsRedeemStep2Desc": "Enter the amount to redeem (must not exceed the remaining balance).",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsRedeemStep3Title": "Complete redemption",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsRedeemStep3Desc": "Tap 'Redeem'. A confirmation card shows the updated balance.",
  "featureInfoGiftCardsTip1": "Gift cards can also be applied as a payment method directly at the POS terminal during checkout.",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsTitle": "Cash Sessions History",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsDesc": "View the history of all cash sessions. Each session shows the terminal ID, session status, and opening float amount. Use Cash Management for opening, managing, and closing sessions.",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsViewTitle": "Viewing Cash Sessions",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsViewStep1Title": "Browse the session list",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsViewStep1Desc": "View all past and current cash sessions with their terminal ID, status, and opening float.",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsViewStep2Title": "Check session details",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsViewStep2Desc": "Each session entry shows key information about the cash session period.",
  "featureInfoCashSessionsTip1": "For active session management (opening, cash events, closing), use the Cash Management page.",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryTitle": "Daily Financial Summary",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryDesc": "Review a comprehensive daily financial summary. See gross revenue, expenses, net revenue, and transaction count. View revenue breakdown by payment method, cash variance analysis, hourly activity patterns, and session details.",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryNavigateTitle": "Navigating Between Dates",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryNavigateStep1Title": "Use the date arrows",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryNavigateStep1Desc": "Click the left/right arrows in the AppBar to go to the previous or next day.",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryNavigateStep2Title": "Pick a specific date",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryNavigateStep2Desc": "Click the date text in the AppBar to open a date picker and jump to any date.",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryReviewTitle": "Reading the Summary",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryReviewStep1Title": "Check KPI cards",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryReviewStep1Desc": "The top section shows Gross Revenue, Expenses, Net Revenue, and Transaction Count for the selected day.",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryReviewStep2Title": "Review payment breakdown",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryReviewStep2Desc": "The 'Revenue by Payment Method' section shows a breakdown by Cash, Card (Mada, Visa, Mastercard), Store Credit, Gift Card, and Mobile Payment with percentages.",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryReviewStep3Title": "Check cash variance",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryReviewStep3Desc": "The 'Cash Variance' section compares expected vs actual cash. A tolerance of ±5 is shown — larger variances are highlighted.",
  "featureInfoDailySummaryTip1": "The hourly activity chart helps identify peak business hours for staffing decisions.",
  "featureInfoFinReconTitle": "Financial Reconciliation",
  "featureInfoFinReconDesc": "Perform end-of-day financial reconciliation. Review revenue summaries, payment method breakdowns, cash positions, and expenses. Count physical cash using the denomination grid and confirm reconciliation to close the business day.",
  "featureInfoFinReconStepsTitle": "Reconciliation Process",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep1Title": "Select the date",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep1Desc": "Use the date picker in the AppBar to select the day you want to reconcile.",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep2Title": "Review revenue summary",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep2Desc": "Check the Total Revenue, Transaction count, and Average Transaction amount. Review the payment method breakdown with percentages.",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep3Title": "Review expenses",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep3Desc": "Check the total expenses and see the breakdown by category (shown as color-coded chips).",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep4Title": "Count physical cash",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep4Desc": "Enter the count for each denomination in the grid (notes and coins). The total is calculated automatically and compared to the expected cash amount.",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep5Title": "Confirm reconciliation",
  "featureInfoFinReconStep5Desc": "Review the cash variance (difference between counted and expected). Tap 'Confirm Reconciliation' and verify in the confirmation dialog.",
  "featureInfoFinReconTip1": "Cash variance is color-coded: green for matching, red for discrepancies.",
  "featureInfoFinReconTip2": "You can also print the report or export to PDF using the action buttons.",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerTitle": "Transaction Explorer",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerDesc": "Search and analyze all transactions with powerful filters. View sales, returns, voids, and exchanges. Toggle analytics for KPI stats, charts, and daily trend analysis. Tap any transaction to see full details.",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerSearchTitle": "Searching Transactions",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerSearchStep1Title": "Use the search bar",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerSearchStep1Desc": "Type a transaction number or keyword in the search field to filter results.",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerSearchStep2Title": "Apply type and status filters",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerSearchStep2Desc": "Use the Type dropdown (Sale, Return, Void, Exchange) and Status dropdown (Completed, Voided, Pending) to narrow results.",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerSearchStep3Title": "Filter by date range",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerSearchStep3Desc": "Click the date range picker button to select a start and end date. Use 'Clear All Filters' to reset everything.",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerAnalyticsTitle": "Viewing Analytics",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerAnalyticsStep1Title": "Toggle analytics panel",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerAnalyticsStep1Desc": "Click the analytics icon in the AppBar to show or hide the analytics dashboard above the transaction list.",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerAnalyticsStep2Title": "Review KPIs and charts",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerAnalyticsStep2Desc": "The analytics panel shows stats cards, transaction charts, and a daily trend line to help identify patterns.",
  "featureInfoTxExplorerTip1": "Tap any transaction row to navigate to the full transaction detail page.",
  "featureInfoReportsTitle": "Reports & Analytics",
  "featureInfoReportsDesc": "Your analytics hub with today's KPIs, comparison with yesterday, and top products. Navigate to 9 specialized sub-reports for detailed analysis across sales, products, categories, staff, hourly trends, payments, inventory, financials, and customers.",
  "featureInfoReportsNavigateTitle": "Using the Reports Dashboard",
  "featureInfoReportsNavigateStep1Title": "Review today's overview",
  "featureInfoReportsNavigateStep1Desc": "The dashboard shows 6 KPI cards: Revenue, Transactions, Net Revenue, Average Basket, Customers, and Refunds. A 'vs Yesterday' comparison section is below.",
  "featureInfoReportsNavigateStep2Title": "Check Top Products",
  "featureInfoReportsNavigateStep2Desc": "View top-selling products today with a bar chart and ranked list showing quantities and revenue.",
  "featureInfoReportsNavigateStep3Title": "Navigate to sub-reports",
  "featureInfoReportsNavigateStep3Desc": "Use the 3x3 grid to navigate to: Sales Summary, Product Performance, Category Breakdown, Staff Performance, Hourly Sales, Payment Methods, Inventory Report, Financial Report, and Customer Report.",
  "featureInfoReportsTip1": "Use the refresh button in the AppBar and the filter panel to customize the data view.",
  "featureInfoLabelsTitle": "Label Templates",
  "featureInfoLabelsDesc": "Design, manage, and print product labels. Use the WYSIWYG label designer to create custom templates with barcodes, product names, prices, SKUs, logos, QR codes, and more. Print labels directly or queue them for batch printing.",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateTitle": "Creating a Label Template",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep1Title": "Click 'Label Designer'",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep1Desc": "Tap the 'Label Designer' button in the AppBar to open the WYSIWYG designer.",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep2Title": "Set template dimensions",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep2Desc": "Enter a template name, width (mm), and height (mm) for the label.",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep3Title": "Add and arrange elements",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep3Desc": "Click elements from the palette (Barcode, Product Name, Price, SKU, Logo, Custom Text, Expiry Date, Weight, QR Code, Separator Line) to add them to the canvas. Drag elements to position them and adjust sizes in the properties panel.",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep4Title": "Save the template",
  "featureInfoLabelsCreateStep4Desc": "Click 'Save' to store the template. It will appear in the template list.",
  "featureInfoLabelsPrintTitle": "Printing Labels",
  "featureInfoLabelsPrintStep1Title": "Select 'Print Queue' on a template",
  "featureInfoLabelsPrintStep1Desc": "Use the 'Print Queue' action on any template row in the list to navigate to the print screen.",
  "featureInfoLabelsPrintStep2Title": "Configure and print",
  "featureInfoLabelsPrintStep2Desc": "Select products, set quantities, and send to the printer.",
  "featureInfoLabelsTip1": "You can duplicate existing templates (including presets) and customize them for faster creation.",
  "featureInfoDeliveryTitle": "Delivery Integration",
  "featureInfoDeliveryDesc": "Connect with delivery platforms to manage online orders. View KPIs (today's orders, revenue, active/pending/completed), manage platform configurations, and process delivery orders (accept, reject, complete).",
  "featureInfoDeliveryPlatformsTitle": "Managing Delivery Platforms",
  "featureInfoDeliveryPlatformsStep1Title": "Go to the Platforms tab",
  "featureInfoDeliveryPlatformsStep1Desc": "Switch to the 'Platforms' tab to see all configured delivery platforms.",
  "featureInfoDeliveryPlatformsStep2Title": "Toggle or configure platforms",
  "featureInfoDeliveryPlatformsStep2Desc": "Use the toggle switch to enable or disable a platform. Click 'Edit' to modify configuration. Click 'Test' to verify API connectivity.",
  "featureInfoDeliveryPlatformsStep3Title": "Add a new platform",
  "featureInfoDeliveryPlatformsStep3Desc": "Use the 'Add Platform' button or the quick action tile on the Overview tab to set up a new delivery integration.",
  "featureInfoDeliveryOrdersTitle": "Processing Delivery Orders",
  "featureInfoDeliveryOrdersStep1Title": "Go to the Orders tab",
  "featureInfoDeliveryOrdersStep1Desc": "Switch to the 'Orders' tab to see incoming delivery orders. Filter by status (All/Pending/Active/Completed).",
  "featureInfoDeliveryOrdersStep2Title": "Accept or reject orders",
  "featureInfoDeliveryOrdersStep2Desc": "Use the 'Accept' button to accept a pending order. Use 'Reject' to reject with a reason.",
  "featureInfoDeliveryOrdersStep3Title": "Complete orders",
  "featureInfoDeliveryOrdersStep3Desc": "When the order is delivered, use the 'Complete' button to finalize it.",
  "featureInfoDeliveryTip1": "Use the Menu Sync button in the AppBar to synchronize your product catalog with delivery platforms.",
  "featureInfoNotificationsTitle": "Notifications Center",
  "featureInfoNotificationsDesc": "View and manage all system notifications. Filter by category (Order, Inventory, Promotion, System, Payment, Staff) and priority (Low, Normal, High, Urgent). Mark as read, bulk delete, or manage notification preferences.",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageTitle": "Managing Notifications",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep1Title": "Filter notifications",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep1Desc": "Use the category and priority chip filters to narrow down notifications to specific types.",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep2Title": "Mark as read",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep2Desc": "Tap the blue dot icon on an unread notification to mark it as read. Use 'Mark All as Read' in the AppBar to clear all unread.",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep3Title": "Delete notifications",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep3Desc": "Swipe left on a notification to delete it. For bulk deletion, long-press to enter selection mode, select multiple notifications, and tap the delete icon.",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep4Title": "Pull to refresh",
  "featureInfoNotificationsManageStep4Desc": "Pull down on the list to refresh and load new notifications.",
  "featureInfoNotificationsTip1": "The unread count badge in the AppBar shows how many unread notifications you have.",
